  abstract = {In recent years, unmanned aerial vehicles (UAV) have started to take an indispensable role in military and civilian applications both in our country and in the world. It is possible to classify these aerial vehicles into two basic classes, fixed and rotary wing, which are in use actively in many tasks such as observation, attack, agricultural applications, reconnaissance, inspection, rescue and cargo. Rotary wing UAVs generally come to the fore with their lighter weights and smaller dimensions in purposive applications such as vertical-takeoff-landing and hovering flight. The vehicles in this class generally named according to the number of rotors they have, and widely used quad-rotor vehicles (quadcopter) stand out in their class with their high stability and easy controllability. In this context, in order to utilize quad-rotor UAVs more efficiently, their performances need to be researched and analyzed by different disciplines (aerodynamics, structural, acoustic, etc.). The propellers of the rotary wing vehicles are an important study subject as the elements that have the greatest impact on their aerodynamic performances. Propeller performance usually expressed in thrust (CT) and power coefficients (CP). Based on this, in this study, it is aimed to conduct a literature research on the determination of thrust and power coefficients, which are the main performance parameters of the propellers of quad-rotor UAVs, and thus to have a prediction for future studies. In this purpose, firstly, a detailed literature research has conducted and studies focusing on performance analysis of the propellers of the quad-rotor UAVs by applying different methods has presented in detail. Later on, the evaluation of applied methods, results and the observed main parameters has done and forecasts and thoughts about potential future studies has revealed.},
